race.comment: MIRAVAL ROSE (1) is in flying form and can take out the last. She got an easy lead here two back over 1200m and was too sharp but really elevated again last time at Flemington to lead throughout and win the G2 Blazer Stakes. She can land in front again from the inside gate here and they'll do well to run her down from there. ABOUNDING (5) and SPLASH BACK (2) both come through the G2 Stocks Stakes at Moonee Valley. The pace was strong there and SPLASH BACK was given a great ride to win. Back to 1400m probably favours ABOUNDING a touch more and she may have the map favours, but there's little between them. TUILERIES (10) tried hard behind MIRAVAL ROSE last time and does meet her slightly better at the weights. She has claims.
